{"title_page": "Rixos Hotels", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n| name = Rixos Hotels\n| logo = Rixos Hotels logo.png\n| logo_size = \n| logo_alt = \n| logo_caption = \n| logo_padding = \n| image = Rixos KONYA.jpg\n| image_size = \n| image_alt = \n| image_caption = The Rixos Konya in Sel\u00e7uklu\n| trading_name = \n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = <!-- Use ISO 639-1 code, e.g. \"fr\" for French. For multiple names in different languages, use {{Lang|[code]|[name]}}. -->\n| type = \n| ISIN = \n| industry = [[Hospitality]], [[tourism]]\n| genre = \n| founded = 2000 in [[Antalya]], [[Turkey]]\n| founder = Fettah Tamince\n| defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| hq_location = \n| hq_location_city = [[Dubai]]\n| hq_location_country = [[United Arab Emirates]]\n| num_locations = 27\n| num_locations_year = 2016\n| area_served = <!-- or: | areas_served = -->\n| key_people = \n| products = [[Luxury hotel]]s, [[resort]]s\n| brands = \n| production = \n| production_year = <!-- Year of production data (if known) -->\n| services = \n| revenue = \n| revenue_year = <!-- Year of revenue data (if known) -->\n| operating_income = \n| income_year = <!-- Year of operating_income data (if known) -->\n| net_income = <!-- or: | profit = -->\n| net_income_year = <!-- or: | profit_year = --><!-- Year of net_income/profit data (if known) -->\n| assets = \n| assets_year = <!-- Year of assets data (if known) -->\n| equity = \n| equity_year = <!-- Year of equity data (if known) -->\n| owner = <!-- or: | owners = -->\n| num_employees = \n| num_employees_year = <!-- Year of num_employees data (if known) -->\n| parent = \n| divisions = \n| subsid = Rixos World Parks & Entertainment\n| website = {{URL|rixos.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Rixos Hotels''' was established in 2000, and offers 5-star luxury accommodation in 25 hotels, 17 of which are operated as waterfront resorts. \n\n==History==\n[[File:Rixos Al Nasr Tripoli hotel.jpg|thumb|The Rixos Al Nasr in Tripoli, Libya (2010)]]\nRixos Hotels was founded by Fettah Tamince in [[Antalya]], Turkey in 2000. Beginning in 1999, Tamince had a partnership with [[Tevfik Arif]] in the Antalya-based Labada Hotel.<ref name=\"FT\">{{cite news|last1=Strauss|first1=Delphine|title=Turkish police hold 10 in Atat\u00fcrk yacht raid|url=https://www.ft.com/content/2448b03a-cd77-11df-9c82-00144feab49a|work=Financial Times|date=1 October 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"Shaw\">{{cite news|last1=Shaw|first1=Craig|last2=Sentek|first2=Zeynep|title=The Football Leaks Family 2: Hidden partnerships, the family mafia and a future U.S. President|url=http://theblacksea.eu/index.php?idT=88&idC=88&idRec=1279&recType=story|work=The Black Sea|date=20 December 2016}}</ref>\n\nSome of Rixos Hotels' projects have been the product of unofficial joint ventures with Russian investors.<ref>{{cite journal|volume=5 |issue=2|title=Sak\u0131p Sabanc\u0131 International Research Award|url=https://www.brookings.edu/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/20060523sabanci_3a.pdf|via=[[The Brookings Institution]]|accessdate=6 March 2017|journal=Turkish Policy Quarterly|page=36|date=2006}}</ref> In the mid-2000s, Russian American businessman [[Felix Sater]] was appointed senior advisor to the company.<ref name=\"Shaw\"/> In 2009, Antalya mayor [[Menderes T\u00fcrel]] was a chief consultant to Rixos.<ref>{{cite news|title=Yerel se\u00e7imde tekrar Belediye Ba\u015fkan\u0131 se\u00e7ilemeyen hangi eski ba\u015fkan Star Grubu'na dan\u0131\u015fman olarak geliyor?|url=http://medya.haber3.com/secimleri-kaybetti-ama-danisman-oldu--13478h.htm|work=Medyakafe|date=15 June 2009|language=Turkish}}</ref>\n\nBy 2010, the hotel chain had grown to include 14 properties and had gained recognition for hosting the Turkish President and Prime Minister during their vacations.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Bu\u011fra|first1=Ay\u015fe|last2=Sava\u015fkan|first2=Osman|title=New Capitalism in Turkey: The Relationship between Politics, Religion and Business|publisher=Edward Elgar Publishing|isbn=978-1-78347-313-7|page=88|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=N-JnAwAAQBAJ&lpg=PA207&dq=%22rixos%20hotels%22&pg=PA88#v=onepage&q&f=false|language=en}}</ref>\n\nDuring the [[2009\u201310 S\u00fcper Lig]], Rixos was the shirt sponsor for the Turkish football club [[Antalyaspor]]. In 2012, Rixos signed an advertising agreement with Spanish football club [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]], with their logo appearing on footballers' shirts.<ref>{{cite web|title=El Atl\u00e9tico de Madrid llega a un acuerdo publicitario con Rixos Hoteles|url=https://www.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/el-atletico-de-madrid-llega-a-un-acuerdo-publicitario-con-rixos-hoteles|publisher=Club Atl\u00e9tico de Madrid|accessdate=5 March 2017|language=es-ES}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, a joint venture of Sembol-Ekopark \u0130n\u015faat-Fine Otelcilik, companies that Rixos owns shares in, secured rights to develop the [[Golden Horn]] yacht harbor in Istanbul.<ref>{{cite news|title=Rixos Hotels chain wins Istanbul's Golden Horn port tender|url=http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/rixos-hotels-chain-wins-istanbuls-golden-horn-port-tender.aspx?pageID=238&nID=51305&NewsCatID=345|work=H\u00fcrriyet Daily News|date=24 July 2013}}</ref> Rixos joined the [[Global Hotel Alliance]] in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=Rixos Hotels Set To Join Global Hotel Alliance  (GHA)|url=http://www.hospitalitynet.org/news/4059901.html|publisher=Hospitality Net|language=en|date=18 March 2013}}</ref>\n\nRixos relocated its headquarters to Dubai in 2014.<ref name=\"Navdar\">{{cite news|last1=Navdar|first1=Parinaaz|title=Rixos Hotels moves headquarters to Dubai |url=http://www.hoteliermiddleeast.com/22412-rixos-hotels-moves-headquarters-to-dubai/|work=HotelierMiddleEast|date=11 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nBugra Berberoglu is the company's CEO.<ref name=\"Navdar\"/>\n\n==Board of directors==\n*Fettah Tamince, Chairman and founder\n*T. Mutlu Simayli, Vice President\n\n==Properties==\nRixos Hotels operates 27 hotels and holds properties in Azerbaijan, Egypt, Kazakhstan, Russia, Switzerland, Turkey and the UAE.<ref name=\"Fahy\">{{cite news|last1=Fahy|first1=Michael|title=Rixos planning 13 new hotels by 2020 |url=http://www.thenational.ae/business/travel-tourism/rixos-planning-13-new-hotels-by-2020|work=The National|date=12 December 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Shaw\"/> Seven of Rixos Hotels' waterfront resorts were developed by the [[Bayrock Group]].<ref>{{cite web|author1=Bayrock Group LLC|title=Bayrock Group Increases Stake in Midtown Miami Mixed-Use Development|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/bayrock-group-increases-stake-in-midtown-miami-mixed-use-development-52778072.html|publisher=PR Newswire|language=en|date=27 July 2007}}</ref> As of 2016, Rixos Hotels was the largest hotel chain in the East Mediterranean Europe region.<ref>{{cite book|last1=K\u00e1tay|first1=\u00c1kos|last2=R\u00e1tz|first2=Tamara|title=The Routledge Handbook of Hotel Chain Management|date=2016|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-317-61844-7|pages=53\u201354|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9uAeDAAAQBAJ&lpg=PA54&dq=%22rixos%20hotels%22&pg=PA54#v=onepage&q&f=false|language=en}}</ref> The hotel group plans to add 13 hotels by the end of 2020.<ref name=\"Fahy\"/> Amenities at Rixos Hotels properties typically include a [[Turkish bath]].\n\n===Properties in operation===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Properties in operation\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Property\n! scope=\"col\" | Location\n! scope=\"col\" | Country\n! scope=\"col\" | Opened/reopened\n! scope=\"col\" | Notes\n|-\n| Rixos Al Nasr || [[Tripoli]] || Libya || 2010 || In August 2011, during the [[Battle of Tripoli (2011)|Battle of Tripoli]], pro-Gaddafi forces seized the Rixos Al Nasr, trapping an Indian parliamentarian, a US Congressman, and over 30 journalists inside.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sherwood|first1=Harriet|title=Libya conflict: journalists trapped in Tripoli's Rixos hotel|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2011/aug/24/libya-journalists-trapped-tripoli-hotel|work=The Guardian|date=24 August 2011}}</ref> The hotel was seized again during the [[2016 Libyan coup d'\u00e9tat attempt]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Rival faction challenges Libya's UN-backed government in Tripoli|url=http://www.middleeasteye.net/news/rival-faction-challenges-libyas-un-backed-government-tripoli-754810947|work=Middle East Eye|date=15 October 2016|language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n| Rixos Bab Al Bahr || [[Ras Al Khaimah]], [[Al Marjan Island]]<ref name=\"Fahy\"/> || UAE || || \n|-\n| Rixos The Palm Dubai || || UAE || 2012 ||\n|-\n| Rixos Premium Dubai || [[Jumeirah Beach Residence]] || UAE || 2017 ||\n|-\n| Rixos Downtown Antalya || Antalya || Turkey || || \n|-\n| The Land of Legends || Antalya || Turkey ||  || The theme park includes designs from [[Franco Dragone]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Nagraj|first1=Aarti|title=Rixos, Emaar open mega Turkish theme park \u2018The Land of Legends\u2019 - Gulf Business|url=http://gulfbusiness.com/emaar-owned-turkish-theme-park-land-legends-opens/|work=Gulf Business|date=25 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Antalya's Land of Legends offers fun for the family|url=https://www.dailysabah.com/life/2016/07/24/antalyas-land-of-legends-offers-fun-for-the-family|work=DailySabah|date=24 July 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| Rixos Premium Tekirova || [[Tekirova]] || Turkey || || \n|-\n| Rixos Premium Belek || [[Belek]] || Turkey || || \n|-\n| Rixos Pera Istanbul Hotel || [[Beyo\u011flu]], Istanbul || Turkey || 2012 ||\n|-\n| Rixos Premium Bodrum || [[Bodrum]] || Turkey || ||\n|-\n| Rixos Premium Gocek || [[G\u00f6cek, Fethiye]] || Turkey || ||\n|-\n| Rixos Hotel Labada || near [[\u00c7amyuva]] || Turkey || || \n|-\n| Rixos Konya || [[Konya]] || Turkey || ||\n|-\n| Rixos Sungate || [[Beldibi, Konyaalt\u0131|Beldibi]] || Turkey || || \n|-\n| Rixos Beldibi || Beldibi || Turkey || || \n|-\n| Rixos Grand Ankara Hotel || Ankara || Turkey || || Built in 1960; formerly known as the Grand Ankara Hotel.\n|-\n| Rixos Libertas Dubrovnik || [[Dubrovnik]] || Croatia || || Formerly known as the Grand Libertas; purchased by Rixos in 2004.<ref>{{cite book|title=Dubrovnik: The Bradt City Guide|year=2007|publisher=Bradt Travel Guides|isbn=978-1-84162-191-3|page=[https://archive.org/details/dubrovnikbradtci0000letc/page/97 97]|url=https://archive.org/details/dubrovnikbradtci0000letc|url-access=registration|quote=rixos hotels.|language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n| Rixos Fl\u00fcela Davos || [[Davos]] || Switzerland || ||\n|-\n| Rixos Bomonti Residence || Istanbul || Turkey || 2012 || The Rixos Bomonti was a US$137.2 million project developed with \u0130pek-\u00c7ak\u0131rkaya, Ayayd\u0131n Group, Mertta\u015f Yap\u0131, and Maslak Yap\u0131.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Knights|first1=Jamie|title=Rixos Hotels expands into Istanbul {{!}} HotelierMiddleEast.com|url=http://www.hoteliermiddleeast.com/7146-rixos-hotels-expands-into-istanbul/|work=HotelierMiddleEast.com|date=26 January 2010}}</ref>\n|-\n| Rixos Borjomi || [[Borjomi]] || Georgia || ||\n|-\n| Rixos President Astana || [[Astana]] || Kazakhstan || ||\n|-\n| Rixos Almaty Hotel || [[Almaty]] || Kazakhstan || ||\n|-\n| Rixos Khadisha Shymkent || [[Shymkent]] || Kazakhstan || ||\n|-\n| Rixos Borovoe || [[Borovoe]] || Kazakhstan || 2012 ||\n|-\n| Rixos Sharm el Sheikh || [[Sharm El Sheikh]] || Egypt || 2012 ||\n|-\n| Rixos Alamein || [[El Alamein]] || Egypt || ||\n|-\n| Rixos Premium Seagate Sharm || [[Sharm El Sheikh]] || Egypt || 2015 ||\n|-\n| Rixos Krasnaya Polyana Sochi || [[Krasnaya Polyana, Sochi, Krasnodar Krai|Krasnaya Polyana]], [[Sochi]] || Russia || ||\n|-\n| Mriya Resort || || Ukraine || ||\n|-\n| Rixos Eski\u015fehir Spa and Thermal Hotel || [[Eski\u015fehir]] || Turkey || 2013 || \n|-\n| Rixos Quba Azerbaijan || [[Quba]] || Azerbaijan || 2012 ||\n|-\n|  || [[Naftalan, Azerbaijan|Naftalan]] || Azerbaijan || 2014 || <ref>{{cite news|title=President Aliyev, first lady review conditions at new block of Naftalan Hotel by Rixos|url=http://en.trend.az/azerbaijan/society/2323408.html|work=Trend.Az|date=18 October 20