{"title_page": "Theo de Lange", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}}\n{{Infobox sailor\n  | name           = Theo de Lange\n  | image          = Soling Podium North Americans 2019 downwind.png\n  | image_size     = \n  | caption        = Theo de Lange pumping the [[guy (sailing)|spinnaker guy]] on the last downwind during the 2019 North Americans Soling Championship.\n  | birth_name     =\n  | fullname       = Theodorus Adrianus de Lange\n  | nickname       = Delange\n  | nationality    = {{NED}}\n  | birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1960|3|16}}\n  | birth_place    = [[Kralingen]], [[Rotterdam]]\n  | death_date     =\n  | death_place    =\n  | height         = {{convert|1.92|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n  | weight         =\n  | retired        =\n  | classes        = [[Vaurien]]<br />[[Finn (dinghy)|Finn]]<br />[[Soling]]\n  | club           = [[:nl:Watersport Vereniging Rotterdam|Watersport Vereniging Rotterdam]]\n  | collegeteam    =\n  | coach          =\n  | medaltemplates-title =\n  | medaltemplates = \n    {{Medal|Country|{{NED}}}}\n      {{MedalCompetition|Vintage Yachting Games}}\n        {{Medal|Gold|2018 Hellerup|Soling<ref name=\"2018Manage2Sail\" />}}\n      {{MedalCompetition|North American Championships}}\n        {{Medal|Gold|2019 Kingston, Ontario|Soling<ref name=\"T\" />}}\n  | show-medals    = yes\n  | updated        = 8 March 2020\n}}\n\n'''Theodorus \"Theo\" Adrianus de Lange''' (born 16 March 1960 in [[Kralingen]], [[Rotterdam]]) is a [[sailor]] from the [[Netherlands]], who represented his country at the [[2018 Vintage Yachting Games]] in [[Hellerup]] [[Denmark]]. De Lange as middleman together with [[helmsman]] [[Rudy den Outer]] and [[Gabor Helmhout]] on the [[foredeck]] took the [[Gold medal]] in the [[Soling]]. During the [[Soling North American Championship results (2010\u201319)#2019 Final results|2019 North American Championship]] in [[Kingston, Ontario]]<ref name=\"T\" /><ref name=\"2019WorldSailing\" /><ref name=\"2019CORK\" /><ref name=\"2019Scuttlebutt\" /><ref name=\"2019SailingNews\" /><ref name=\"2019SailingAnarchy\" /><ref name=\"2019CISA\" />, De Lange again as middleman in the Dutch Soling ''Sophie\u2019s Choice'' together with helmsman Rudy den Outer but now with [[Thies Bosch]] on the foredeck took first place. This was the first time [[Europe|European]] sailors won this championship in the over fifty years history of the North American Soling Championship!\n\nDe Lange became in 2000, together with Rudy den Outer and [[Leo Determan]], the last [[Soling National Champions|Dutch Champion]]s during the Olympic Soling era. <ref name=\"RZV\" /> Theo is since 2018 also one of the [[International Soling Association#ISA Committee|elected International Soling Association committee members]].\n\n== Personal life ==\nDe Lange lives and works in [[Capelle aan den IJssel]], earned a degree in law at the [[Erasmus University]] [[Rotterdam]], is married and has two daughters.\n{{Footer North American Champions Soling}}\n{{Footer Winners Vintage Yachting Games}}\n{{Footer Dutch Championship Winners in Soling}}\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs =\n <ref name=T>{{cite web\n   |url=http://www.soling.com/results/ShowResults.asp?ID=1132\n   |title=North American Championship / CORK, Kingston 07/08/2019 To 11/08/2019. / Rk=1.5\n   |year=2019\n   |website=www.soling.com\n   |publisher=International Soling Association\n   |location=Buenos Aires (ARG)\n   |access-date=1 March 2020\n }}</ref>\n  <ref name             = RZV> {{cite web\n    | title             = GALERIJ der KAMPIOENEN \n    | language          = NL\n    | publisher         = Rotterdamsche Zeil Vereeniging\n    | url               = http://ym4wi1n1c458giop38sj11f0-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/GALERIJ-der-KAMPIOENEN-4.pdf\n    | website           = rzv.nl\n    | accessdate        = 8 March 2020\n  }}</ref>\n  <ref name             = 2019WorldSailing> {{cite web\n    | year              = 2019\n    | title             = Soling 